<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I was basing mine off of when things break stun and run toward you...and there is no way any of the ones up to and including Sound of Force last 8 seconds.  If they did then at 50 you should be able to SoF a mob and start casting retribution and retribution would hit before the mob started to move at all toward you...but that doesn't happen.

Go cast Sound of Force on a mob at a distance and immediately cast reckoning if you really want to test it...1 second roughly delay for all spells to repop after stun (not counting the stun itself) and 7 seconds for reckoning...if the mob runs at you and interupts your spell (which it will), then it obviously wasn't stunned for 8 seconds  ;)

